step.action:
Through natural PM-style conversation, refine and capture:
      - {{problem_statement}}
      - {{target_users}}
      - {{expected_outcome}}
      - {{business_value}}
      - {{constraints}}
      - {{scope_in}}
      - {{scope_out}}
      - {{success_signals}}

Define a single epic with:
      - {{epic_name}}
      - {{epic_summary}}
      - {{epic_goal}}
      - {{epic_priority}}
      - {{epic_success_metrics}}

Capture workspace-level technical outputs:
      - {{cross_story_dependencies}}
      - {{technical_risks}}
      - {{open_questions}}
      - {{recommended_implementation_order}}

For each story in {{stories}}, prepare {{story_md_content}} with this structure:

# Story: {{story.title}}
> Feature: {{feature_title}} | ID: {{story.id}} | Priorité: {{story.priority}}

## Contexte
{{story.user_outcome}}

## Acceptance Criteria
{{story.acceptance_criteria as numbered list}}

## Contraintes applicables
- DoD : context/dod.md
- NFR : {relevant NFR constraints for this story, extracted from context/nfr.md}

## Tasks
{{for each task in story.tasks:
  "- [ ] [{{task.kind}}] {{task.title}}
        {{task.description}}
        {{if task.technical_notes: '      Note: ' + task.technical_notes}}
        {{if task.depends_on: '      Dépend de: ' + task.depends_on | join(', ')}}"
}}

## Notes architecturales
{{story.architecture_notes or "Aucune"}}

## Risques
{{story.risks or "Aucun identifié"}}

---
Created via Nakiros plan-feature on {date}. Execute with /nak-workflow-dev-story.

check.action:
Build {{ux_md_content}} in {{document_language}}:

# UX — {{feature_title}}
> Planned by Nakiros plan-feature on {date}. Refine with /nak-workflow-create-ux-design.

## Screens & Flows
{List each screen or view involved in this feature — name, purpose, entry point — grounded in the stories.}

## Key Interactions
{Forms, modals, tables, navigation patterns needed per story — tied to acceptance criteria.}

## Layout
{Layout approach per screen: full-page, sidebar, modal, drawer, split-view…}

## Empty & Error States
{How each screen should handle empty, loading, and error states.}

## Component Needs
{UI components required for this feature — reference existing components from design-system.md when available.}

## UX Decisions Made
{Explicit UX choices surfaced during PM discovery: what is shown, what is hidden, what is prioritised.}

## Open UX Questions
{Interactions or states that need design validation before implementation.}

---
Bootstrapped from plan-feature. Run /nak-workflow-create-ux-design for a full UX specification.

step.action:
Write the following files using your native Write tool (create parent directories as needed):
      - `{{preview_root}}/feature.md` ← feature.md content (new or updated with {{stories_table_rows}}). If {feature_dir}/feature.md already exists, load it first and replace only the Stories table section. Otherwise create it from the standard template populated from {{feature_title}}, {{epic_summary}}, and {{stories_table_rows}}.
      - For each story: `{{preview_root}}/stories/{{story.id}}.md` ← {{story_md_content}}
      - If {{has_frontend_scope}} is true: `{{preview_root}}/ux.md` ← {{ux_md_content}}
      - If {{has_frontend_scope}} is true: `{{preview_root}}/mockup.html` ← {{mockup_html_content}}

step.output:
[PLAN-FEATURE] ✅ TERMINÉ
Feature : {{feature_title}}
Stories : {{stories | count}}
{{for each story: "  - {{story.id}} — {{story.title}}"}}
{{if has_frontend_scope: "🎨 UX + maquette HTML dans le context"}}

Prochaine étape : /nak-workflow-dev-story pour implémenter une story.
